<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-61-0414 </DOCNO><TEXT>A computerized method for applying gradient pulses in NMR imaging is proposed,especially for medical diagnosis, although application to industrialnondestructive testing is feasible. The method overcomes drawbacks associatedwith the difficulties involved in programming gradient reels, which oftenpreclude the use of oblique images to the detriment of the quality ofdiagnosis.</TEXT></DOC>